content: Trump slams Berkeley after violent protests

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div div span
html body div article div div div div section div div div div h3 span
html body div article div div div div section div div div div ul li span
content: Two College Republicans attacked during next-day interview

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div div ul li span
content: Breitbart editor applauds Trump threat to cut federal funding

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div p cite span
html body div article div div div div section div div p span
content: Protests that erupted at UC Berkeley ahead of a planned Wednesday appearance by right-wing commentator Milo Yiannopoulos caused $100,000 worth of damage to the campus, the school said Thursday.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div span
content: The university blamed "150 masked agitators" for the unrest, saying they had come to campus to disturb an otherwise peaceful protest.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div span
content: Two Berkeley College Republicans "were attacked while conducting an interview" on the campus on Thursday, UC Berkeley also said in a prepared statement. The attackers, who were not affiliated with the university, were taken into custody by UC Berkeley police.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div span
content: Administrators decided to cancel the Wednesday event about two hours before the Breitbart editor's speech. UC Berkeley said it removed him from campus "amid the violence and destruction of property and out of concern for public safety."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div span
content: Black-clad protesters wearing masks threw commercial-grade fireworks and rocks at police. Some even hurled Molotov cocktails that ignited fires. They also smashed windows of the student union center on the Berkeley campus where the Yiannopoulos event was to be held.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div div span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: At least six people were injured. Some were attacked by the agitators -- who are a part of an anarchist group known as the "Black Bloc" that has been causing problems in Oakland for years, said Dan Mogulof, UC Berkeley spokesman.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: More than 1,500 protesters had gathered at Sproul Plaza, chanting and holding signs that read: "No safe space for racists" and "This is war."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: The violent protesters tore down metal barriers, set fires near the campus bookstore and damaged the construction site of a new dorm. One woman wearing a red Trump hat was pepper sprayed in the face while being interviewed by

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div a span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: She was able to respond that she was OK after the

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: As the scene spiraled out of control, university

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: police warned protesters to disperse and issued a lockdown for campus buildings.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "We condemn in the strongest possible terms the violence and unlawful behavior that was on display and deeply regret that those tactics will now overshadow the efforts to engage in legitimate and lawful protest against the performer's presence and perspectives," UC Berkeley

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div a span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "While Yiannopoulos' views, tactics and rhetoric are profoundly contrary to our own, we are bound by the Constitution, the law, our values and the campus's Principles of Community to enable free expression across the full spectrum of opinion and perspective," it stated.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: As police dispersed the crowd from campus, a remaining group of protesters

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: moved into downtown Berkeley and smashed windows at several local banks.

content: 'I just want to burn it down'

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div div div div span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: Yiannopoulos had been invited to speak by the Berkeley College Republicans. He has been on a college speaking tour and had planned to speak about cultural appropriation on Wednesday.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: In a Facebook Live video, Yiannopoulos described what happened as "an expression of political violence."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "I'm just stunned that hundreds of people ... were so threatened by the idea that a conservative speaker might be persuasive, interesting, funny and might take some people with him, they have to shut it down at all costs."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: President Donald Trump weighed in on Twitter, suggesting the possibility of cutting federal funds to the public university.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "If U.C. Berkeley does not allow free speech and practices violence on innocent people with a different point of view -- NO FEDERAL FUNDS?" Trump tweeted Thursday morning.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: Later, Yiannopoulos posted Trump's tweet to Facebook and proclaimed himself "the catalyst for this change."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "American universities are on notice. The President is watching," he wrote. "The days you could silence conservative and libertarian voices on campus and still expect to collect their tax money are coming to an end."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div a span
content: Yiannopoulos trying to convince colleges hate speech is cool

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: But some protesters said the Yiannopoulos event wasn't a matter of free speech, because he espouses hate speech.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: UC Berkeley said it had prepared security measures following what had happened at Yiannopoulos' previous events. One of his planned speaking engagements at UC Davis was also canceled last month in response to protests.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div div div span a span
content: Protesters shut down Milo Yiannopoulos event at UC Davis

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "Ultimately, and unfortunately, however, it was impossible to maintain order given the level of threat, disruption and organized violence," UC Berkeley said in a statement.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div h3 span
html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: Most UC Berkeley students who spoke with CNN said they were relieved that Yiannopoulos wasn't able to speak, but this was not how they wanted to accomplish that goal.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: One student told CNN that he didn't agree with what happened.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "It's a sad irony in the fact that the Free Speech Movement was founded here and tonight, someone's free speech got shut down. It might have been hateful speech, but it's still his right to speak," said Shivam Patel, a freshmen who stood outside of Sproul Plaza.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: The Free Speech Movement started at UC Berkeley in 1964 after students protested en masse when administrators tried to restrict their political activities on campus.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: Patel said he supported peaceful protests, but disagreed with the way things turned out on Wednesday.

tag: html body div article div div div div section div div div span
content: "It allows people on the right to say, 'Look at all these liberal Berkeley snowflakes. They're intolerant of speech.' I don't think it's productive at all. It does nothing to help this country."

tag: html body div article div div div div section div p span
content: CNN's Jamiel Lynch and Stephanie Becker contributed to this report.
